data.name: OmrGradeCalculatorOverview
data.value: Aspose.OMR Grade Calculator is a free online app to easily calculate quiz, test and assignments scores from any device and platform. Enter the total number of questions and the number of wrong answers to get the detailed score information. This grading tool supports two grading systems: standard 5 points and 12 points extended with +/- marks. Use grading chart for a quick reference of grades distribution.

data.name: OmrCreateOverview
data.value: Aspose.OMR Create is a free online app that allows creating customized OMR images from any device and platform. You can choose to make answer sheets, survey forms or test forms. You can save OMR images in PDF or PNG format. Use Aspose.OMR Scan to get results from photos and scans of filled forms.

data.name: OmrCreateAnswerSheetOverview
data.value: Aspose.OMR Create Answer Sheet is a free online app that allows creating customized answer sheet forms from any device and platform. Answer sheets can be used in a test, examination, quiz or assignments for quick and easy marking students' answers. You can save Answer Sheet in PDF or PNG format. Use Aspose.OMR Scan Answer Sheet to get results from photos and scans of filled forms.

data.name: OmrCreateAnswerSheetOverview2
data.value: This free application is intended to build any kind of OMR sheets like admission forms, feedbacks, assessments, multiple choice question examinations. Students mark their answers, or other personal information, by darkening circles marked on a pre-printed sheet. Due to its extremely low error rate, low cost and ease-of-use, OMR is a popular method of tallying votes. All OMR forms created by our software are printable, so you can use them offline for data filling by your clients. It is extremely important to print sheets as they were designed, so PDF format is the best choice for this purpose.

data.name: OmrCreateAnswerSheetOverview3
data.value: Aspose.OMR Create Answer Sheet allows flexibility in building your own customized answer sheets. We offer a variety of sample forms that are available for you to create in our application. These sample forms can give you a great foundation for creating your own forms. It's absolutely free application though it has some restrictions related to questions count and overall volume of printable information. See video below to get quick insight about an answer sheet creation with our app.

data.name: OmrCreateSurveyOverview
data.value: Aspose.OMR Create Survey is a free online app that allows creating survey forms from any device and platform. Frequently used customer satisfaction survey is designed for companies and advertising agencies to learn more about your customer and your product. Created survey can be saved in PDF and PNG formats. Use Aspose.OMR Scan Survey to get results from photos and scans of filled survey forms.

data.name: OmrCreateTestOverview
data.value: Aspose.OMR Create Test is a free online app that allows creating test forms from any device and platform. Test form contains various elements, including Grid ID, text questions and Answer sheet section. Created test can be saved in PDF and PNG formats. Use Aspose.OMR Scan Test to get results from photos and scans of filled testing forms.

data.name: OmrScanOverview
data.value: Aspose.OMR Scan is a free online app that allows scanning omr images that were created using Create app. Upload photo or scan of your OMR sheet, select the type of omr template and it will be recognized with high precision. Recognition results can be copied or saved in popular formats: CSV, JSON. Scan Answer Sheet works on any device and platform and has no extra requirements.

data.name: OmrScanAnswerSheetOverview

Recognition results can be copied or saved in popular formats: CSV, JSON. Scan Answer Sheet works on any device and platform and has no extra requirements.

data.name: OmrScanAnswerSheetOverview2
data.value: On this step you are already have printed and filled answer sheets created on the previous step in our free Aspose.OMR Create Answer Sheet application. Now it is time to process the forms with this free app. Aspose.OMR Scan Answer Sheet accommodates for human error in filling in bubbles imprecisely — as long as they do not stray into the other bubbles and the bubble is almost filled, the scanner will detect it as filled in. Optical mark recognition is a time saving process and allows collecting data accurately.

data.name: OcrExtensionRelatedBlockTitle_jpg
data.value: Joint Photographic Expert Group Image File

data.name: OcrExtensionRelatedBlockContent_jpg
data.value: A JPEG is a type of image format that is saved using the method of lossy compression. The output image, as result of compression, is a trade-off between storage size and image quality. Users can adjust the compression level to achieve the desired quality level while at the same time reduce the storage size. Image quality is negligibly affected if 10:1 compression is applied to the image. The higher the compression value, the higher the degradation in image quality.

data.name: OcrExtensionRelatedBlockContent_png
data.value: PNG, Portable Network Graphics, refers to a type of raster image file format that use lossless compression. This file format was created as a replacement of Graphics Interchange Format (GIF) and has no copyright limitations. However, PNG file format does not support animations. PNG file format supports loseless image compression that makes it popular among its users. With the passage of time, PNG has evolved as one of the mostly used image file format.

data.name: OcrExtensionRelatedBlockContent_bmp
data.value: Files having extension .BMP represent Bitmap Image files that are used to store bitmap digital images. These images are independent of graphics adapter and are also called device independent bitmap (DIB) file format. This independency serves the purpose of opening the file on multiple platforms such as Microsoft Windows and Mac. The BMP file format can store data as two-dimensional digital images in both monochrome as well as color format with various colour depths.

data.name: OcrExtensionRelatedBlockContent_tiff
data.value: TIFF or TIF, Tagged Image File Format, represents raster images that are meant for usage on a variety of devices that comply with this file format standard. It is capable of describing bilevel, grayscale, palette-color and full-color image data in several color spaces. It supports lossy as well as lossless compression schemes to choose between space and time for applications using the format.

data.name: OcrExtensionRelatedBlockContent_gif
data.value: A GIF or Graphical Interchange Format is a type of highly compressed image. Owned by Unisys, GIF uses the LZW compression algorithm that does not degrade the image quality. For each image GIF typically allow up to 8 bits per pixel and up to 256 colours are allowed across the image. In contrast to a JPEG image, which can display up to 16 million colours and fairly touches the limits of the human eye.

data.name: OcrExtensionRelatedBlockContent_emf
data.value: Enhanced metafile format (EMF) stores graphical images device-independently. Metafiles of EMF comprises of variable-length records in chronological order that can render the stored image after parsing on any output device. These variable-length records can be definitions of enclosed objects, commands for drawing, and graphics properties critical to render the image accurately.

data.name: OcrExtensionRelatedBlockContent_svg
data.value: SVG files are Scalable Vector Graphics Files that use XML based text format for describing the appearance of image. The word Scalable refers to the fact that the SVG can be scaled to different sizes without losing any quality. Text based description of such files make them independent of resolution. It is one of the mostly used format for building website and print graphics in order to achieve scalability.

data.name: OcrExtensionRelatedBlockContent_eps
data.value: Files with EPS extension essentially describe an Encapsulated PostScript language program that describes the appearance of a single page. The name "Encapsulated" because it can be included or encapsulated in another PostScript language page description. This script based file format may contain any combination of text, graphics and images.

data.value: Aspose.Barcode Generator is a free online application to generate barcodes of 60+ supported barcode symbologies, both 1D barcode types and 2D barcode types. It fast an easy way of adding machine reading tags to your documents and products. It supports both raster and vector output image formats.

data.name: BarcodeRecognizeAppFullDescription
data.value: Aspose.Barcode Reader is a free online application to read barcodes from image or your mobile phone's camera. It supports 60+ barcode symbologies including all the popular ones. It is able to locate and read multiple barcodes on image. Our sophisticated algorithm allows you to read even damaged barcodes.
